  "prompt": "How do I collect movie tickets booked on BookMyShow?",
  "response": "The way you collect your movie tickets booked on BookMyShow depends on the option you chose during the booking process. Here's a breakdown of the common methods:\n\n**1. Mobile Ticket (QR Code):**\n\n*   **How it Works:** This is the most common and convenient option. You'll receive a confirmation email and an SMS with a QR code.\n*   **Collection Process:**\n    *   **Show the QR Code:** At the cinema entrance, look for the attendant with the ticket scanner. Simply show them the QR code on your smartphone screen. They will scan it, and you're good to go!\n    *   **No Printout Needed:** This is a paperless option, so you don't need to print anything.\n    *   **If you can't access the QR code:** Contact BookMyShow customer support immediately or the cinema staff for assistance. Make sure you have your booking ID handy.\n\n**2. Print At Home:**\n\n*   **How it Works:**  During booking, you'll select the \"Print at Home\" option. You'll receive a PDF attachment in your confirmation email.\n*   **Collection Process:**\n    *   **Print the PDF:** Download the PDF from your email and print it. Make sure the entire ticket, including the barcode, is printed clearly.\n    *   **Present the Printout:** Take the printed ticket to the cinema entrance and hand it over to the attendant.\n\n**3. Box Office Pickup:**\n\n*   **How it Works:** You choose to collect your tickets from the cinema's box office.\n*   **Collection Process:**\n    *   **Go to the Box Office:** Head to the cinema's box office counter.\n    *   **Provide Booking Details:** Tell the staff your booking ID (confirmation number) or show them the confirmation SMS/email on your phone. You might also need to show a valid photo ID (e.g., driver's license, passport, Aadhaar card).\n    *   **Collect Your Tickets:** The staff will verify your details and hand you your printed tickets.\n    *   **Arrive Early:**  Arrive well in advance of the movie start time to avoid long queues at the box office.\n\n**Important Tips and Considerations:**\n\n*   **Check Your Confirmation Email/SMS:** Always refer to your confirmation email/SMS from BookMyShow for specific instructions related to your booking. It will clearly state how to collect your tickets.\n*   **Booking ID/Confirmation Number:** Keep your booking ID (also known as confirmation number or PNR) handy, regardless of the collection method. You'll need it for reference or if any issues arise.\n*   **Valid Photo ID:** Carry a valid photo ID if you opted for box office pickup, or if the cinema specifies it in the booking confirmation.\n*   **Network Connectivity:** Ensure you have a stable internet connection on your phone when using the mobile ticket option, so you can access the QR code.\n*   **Contact BookMyShow Support:** If you encounter any problems, don't hesitate to contact BookMyShow's customer support for assistance. You can usually find their contact details on their website or in your booking confirmation.\n*   **Cinema Instructions:**  Some cinemas may have their own specific procedures for ticket collection. Pay attention to any signs or instructions provided at the cinema.\n* **Avoid Screenshots:** Sometimes screenshots of QR codes don't work as well as showing the code directly from the app or email.\n\nBy following these guidelines, you should have a smooth ticket collection experience!\n",
